The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 UN translator held for fraud

 New York, Aug. 6 (Reuters): US authorities arrested a UN translator on suspicion of visa fraud today, accusing him of using UN letterhead to bring foreigners into the US for non-existent conferences.

 Vyacheslav Manokhin, a Russian translator of documents at the New York headquarters, was arrested today along with Vladimir Derevianko, who is accused of scheming with Manokhin to prepare false documents submitted to U. immigration officials, federal prosecutors said.

 A third man, Kamiljan Tursunov, is accused of paying $15,000 for a fraudulent visa. He also faces conspiracy and fraud charges, the US attorney in Manhattan said.




